        "committer": {
          "name": "Daniel Kobras",
          "email": "d.kobras@science-computing.de",
          "date": "2015-04-13 09:47:42.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-6459 osd-zfs: fix build errors with ZoL 0.6.4",
        "message": "LU-6459 osd-zfs: fix build errors with ZoL 0.6.4\n\nSome memory management changes in the ZFS on Linux release 0.6.4 lead\nto build errors with Lustre 2.5.3. This patch backports the necessary\ncompatibility changes that went into the Lustre master branch:\n\n- Instead of preventing the inclusion of the kmem.h header by setting\n  a guard, the kmem_cache_* preprocessor macros are explictly\n  undefined to make the Linux interface available.\n\n  Backported from master:\n  Lustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/13096\n  Lustre-commit: 5a758a40de3b6b4e0aeb082195f61d86536233d2\n\n- The sa_spill_alloc()/sa_spill_free() interfaces have been retired.\n  Callers may either use the more memory efficient zio_buf_alloc()/\n  zio_buf_free() which are now exported, or they may use their own\n  allocator.\n\n  For the purposes of this patch an osd_zio_buf_alloc()/\n  osd_zio_buf_free() wrapper function was introduced which layers on\n  whichever interface is provided.\n\n  Backported from master:\n  Lustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/13097\n  Lustre-commit: c994fc0df788928c18485be34b28f40c34538ee8\n\nSigned-off-by: Daniel Kobras <d.kobras@science-computing.de>\nChange-Id: I9c9012dc523d3d399167d02a0f58ef4ef66e3ba1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
